# Monitor runtime data (user-specific snapshots)
data/

# Environment — DENY-ALL, then allow back only the placeholder template.
# Safer than listing variants: an unlisted name (.env.production, .env.local.bak,
# .env.staging) was previously committable. Everything is ignored by default now;
# `.env.example` is the single deliberate exception and must hold no real values.
.env*
*.env
!.env.example

